tweet.text:
There’s a set of founders in SaaS that have really defied gravity and built empires. 

@tobi  - Shopify ($SHOP)
@alighodsi - Databricks ($TBD)
@oliveur - Datadog ($DDOG)
@George_Kurtz - CrowdStrike ($CRWD)
@eastdakota - Cloudflare ($NET)

Common traits?

1) Built a culture that can retain founder-types in management positions (and thus spawns founders)

2) Targeted a huge, expanding TAM (e-com, data, cloud spend, cyber spend, web traffic)

3) Found the perfect entry point (storefront, Spark, Infra monitoring, EDR, CDN/DNS)

4) Empire built ferociously- always launching new products, always a grand ten year plan 

5) Incredibly responsive on email (at least the two I’ve interacted with the most)

What else? Who did I miss?
